messages.content: is angular frequency and angular velocity the same

- **Angular Frequency (\( \omega \))**: Often related to oscillations and waves, expressed in radians per second. It describes how fast something oscillates.

- **Angular Velocity (\( \omega \))**: Related to rotational motion, also expressed in radians per second. It refers to the rate of rotation around a point.

While the symbols and units can overlap, their contexts differ.
